Even though they only played 14 championships, they are still the 6th most successful team in Argentine football history, if counting amateur championships.

==Rugby union==
Kept as a social club for several years, Alumni started a youth [[rugby union]] team in 1951, which achieved good results. In 1960 the club presented a team that won the third division of the [[Unión de Rugby de Buenos Aires|Buenos Aires league]], reaching the second division. The club would later climb up to first division and win 5 titles; 4 consecutive between 1989 and 1992, and in 2001.

In 2002, Alumni won its first [[Nacional de Clubes|Nacional]] title, defeating Jockey of Rosario 23-21 in the final.

===Honours===
