'''August''' {{Audio|En-us-August.ogg|(pronunciation)}} is the eighth [[month]] of the [[year]] in the [[Julian calendar|Julian]] and [[Gregorian Calendar]]s and one of seven months with a length of 31 days.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/42820/August August].&quot; ''Encyclopedia Britannica''. 2008. [[Encyclopædia Britannica Online]]. 23 September 2008.&lt;/ref&gt;

This month was originally named ''[[Sextilis]]'' in [[Latin]], because it was the sixth month in the original ten-month [[Roman calendar]] under [[Romulus and Remus|Romulus]] in 753 BC, when [[March]] was the first month of the year. About 700&amp;nbsp;BC it became the eighth month when [[January]] and [[February]] were added to the year before March by King [[Numa Pompilius]], who also gave it 29 days. [[Julius Caesar]] added two days when he created the [[Julian calendar]] in [[45 BC]] giving it its modern length of 31 days. In [[8 C]] it was [[Augustus#Month of August|renamed]] in honor of [[Augustus]], who did ''not'' take a day from February (see the [[Julian calendar#Debunked theory on month lengths|debunked theory on month lengths]]). He chose this month to take his name rather than his birth month - which was traditional - as a mark of honour to the defeated Queen [[Cleopatra]] the last ruler of Egypt, this being her birth month. 

In the [[Southern Hemisphere]], August is the seasonal equivalent of [[February]] in the [[Northern Hemisphere]].

In common years no other month starts on the same day of the week as August, though in leap years February starts on the same day. August ends on the same day of the week as November every year.

==Other names==
* In [[Afrikaans language|Afrikaans]], the month is called ''{{lang|af|augustus}}''
* In [[Albanian language|Albanian]], the month is called ''{{lang|al|Gusht}}''
* In [[Arabic language|Arabic]], the month is called {{lang|ar-Arab|أغسطس}} ''{{transl|ar|ISO|ʾUġusṭuṣ}}'' or {{lang|ar-Arab|آب}} ''{{transl|ar|ISO|[[Av|ʾĀb]]}}''; usage varies from place to place and person to person.
* In [[Azerbaijani language|Azerbaijani]], the month is called Avqust.
* In [[Basque language|Basque]], the month is called Abuztua.
* In [[Bulgarian language|Bulgarian]], the month is known as ''{{lang|bg-Cyrl|Август}}''
* In [[Catalan language|Catalan]], the month is called ''{{lang|cs|agost}}'' from the Latin ''{{lang|la|Augustus}}''.
* In [[Chinese language|Chinese]], the month is known as ''{{lang|zh-Hans|八月}}'' meaning, simply, &quot;eighth month.&quot;
* In [[Croatian language|Croatian]], the month is called ''{{lang|hr|Kolovoz}}''
* In [[Czech language|Czech]], the month is called ''{{lang|cs|srpen}}''
* In [[Danish language|Danish]] the month is called ''{{lang|nl|August}}''
* In [[Maldivian language|Dhivehi]], the month is called ''{{lang|dv|Augastu}}''
* In [[Dutch language|Dutch]] the month is called ''{{lang|nl|augustus}}''
* In [[Estonian language|Estonian]] the month is called ''{{lang|et|august}}''
* In [[Filipino language|Filipino]], the month is called ''{{lang|tl|agosto}}'', from a Spanish origin
* In [[Finnish language|Finnish]], the month is called ''{{lang|fi|elokuu}}'', meaning &quot;harvest month&quot;
* In [[French language|French]], the month is called ''{{lang|fr|août}}'' (pronounced &quot;OOT&quot; or just &quot;OO&quot;) derived from the Latin ''{{lang|la|augustus}}''.
* In [[Galician language|Galician]], the month is called Agosto.
* In [[German language|German]], the month is called ''{{lang|de|August}}'' ({{lang|du|August'}})
* In [[Greek language|Greek]], the month is called ''{{lang|el-Latn|Avgoustos}}'' ({{lang|el|Αύγουστος'}})
* In [[Hebrew language|Hebrew]], the month is called ''{{lang|he|Ogust}}'' or ''{{transl|he|ISO|[[Av|Av]]}}'' ({{lang|he|אב}}) - the parallel month in the Jewish calendar.
* In [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]], the month is called ''{{lang|hu|augusztus}}''
* In [[Icelandic language|Icelandic]], the month is called Ágúst.
* In [[Indonesian language|Indonesian]], the month is known as ''{{lang|id|Agustus}}''
* In [[Irish language|Irish]], August is known as ''{{lang|ga|Lúnasa}}'', a modern rendition of [[Lughnasadh]], from the god [[Lugh]].
* In [[Italian language|Italian]], [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] and [[Spanish language|Spanish]], the month is called ''{{lang|und-Latn|agosto}}'' from the Latin ''{{lang|la|Augustus}}''.
* In [[Japanese language|Japanese]], the month is called ''{{transl|ja|Latn|hachigatsu}}'' ({{lang|ja|八月}}), meaning, simply, &quot;eighth month.　In classical Japanese the name is ”葉月”　Meaning, month of leaves&quot;
* In [[Korean language|Korean]], the month is called ''{{transl|ko|Latn|parwol}}'' ({{lang|ko|팔월}}, {{lang|ko-Hans|八月}}) meaning, simply, &quot;eighth month.&quot;
* In [[Latvian language|Latvian]], the month is called ''{{lang|lv|Augusts}}''
* In [[Lithuanian language|Lithuanian]], the month is called ''{{lang|lt|rugpjūtis}}''
* In [[Malay language|Malay]], the month is known as ''{{lang|ms|Ogos}}''
* In [[Maltese language|Maltese]],the month is called  ''{{lang|mt|Awissu}}''
* In [[Persian language|Persian]], the month is called {{lang|fa|اوت و آگوست}} (ut, also Agust)
* In [[Polish language|Polish]], the month is called ''{{lang|pl|sierpień}}'', meaning &quot;[month of the] sickle&quot;.
* In [[Romanian language|Romanian]], the month is called ''{{lang|ro|august}}''
* In [[Russian language|Russian]], the month is called ''{{transl|ro|ISO|avgust}}'' ({{lang|ru-Cyrl|авгуcт}})
* In [[Samoan]], the month is called {{lang|es|aukuso}}
* In [[Serbian language|Serbian]] the month is called ''{{lang|sr-Latn|avgust}}'' ({{lang|sr-Cyrl|авгуcт}})
* In [[Sinhalese language|Sinhalese]] the month is called අගෝස්තු &quot;{{lang|si|agostu}}&quot;
* In [[Slovenian language|Slovenian]], the month is called Avgust.
* In [[Spanish language|Spanish]], the month is called ''{{lang|es|agosto}}''
*In [[Swahili language| Swahili]], the month is called Agosti.
* In [[Swedish language|Swedish]], the month is named ''{{lang|sv|augusti}}'', literally plural of the Latin ''{{lang|la|augustus}}''&amp;nbsp;– &quot;the venerable&quot;.
* In [[Thai language|Thai]], the month is called ''{{lang|th|สิงหาคม}}'' ''{{lang|th|Sing-ha-kom}}'' representing the ''{{lang|th|Singha}}'' (lion)
* In [[Turkish language|Turkish]], the month is called ''{{lang|tr|Ağustos}}''
* In [[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]], the month is called ''{{lang|uk|Серпень}}''
* In [[Vietnamese language|Vietnamese]], the month is called ''{{lang|vi|Thang Tam}}'' (Or simply called the 'Eighth Month')
* In [[Welsh language|Welsh]], the month is called ''{{lang|cy|Awst}}''

==Events in August==
[[File:Les Très Riches Heures du duc de Berry aout.jpg|right|thumb|August, from the [[Très Riches Heures du Duc de Berry]] showing a group of travelers and the Duc's [[Château d'Étampes]] in the background]]
* In the [[neopaganism|neopagan]] [[wheel of the year]] August begins at or near Lughnasadh in the [[northern hemisphere]] and [[Imbolc]] in the [[southern hemisphere]].
* Some of Ireland's most famous battles have been fought in this month. They include: the [[Second Battle of Athenry]] (1316); the [[battle of Knockdoe]] (1504); the [[Battle of the Yellow Ford]] (1596); the First [[Battle of Curlew Pass]] (1599); the [[Battle of Dungans Hill]] (1647); the [[Battle of Castlebar]] (1798), and the [[Battle of the Bogside]] (1969).
* August 1, [[Yorkshire Day]].
* [[August 1]], [[Swiss National Day]], a public holiday in [[Switzerland]].
* [[August 5]], [[International Beer Day]], a holiday in celebration of beer.
* August 6, [[Bolivia]]'s independence day.
* [[August 6]] National Salvadoran-American Day in the United States.
* August 6, 1945, [[Atomic bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki|Hiroshima is bombed]], for the first time in history [[nuclear weapon]] was used against people. The nuclear weapon used on Hiroshima is known as [[Little Boy]].
* August 9, 1945, [[Atomic bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki|Nagasaki is bombed]], this is the second and the last known use of [[nuclear weapon]] against people. The nuclear weapon used on Nagasaki is known as [[Fat Man]].
* August 9, 1965, [[Singapore]] separated from the Federation of Malaysia and became independent.
* [[August 9]] is [[National Women's Day]] in [[South Africa]].
* August 10, 1822, [[Ecuador]] became an independent country.
* August 13, National Left-Handers Day in the United States.
* August 14, 1947, [[Pakistan]] became independent (included East Bengal region as a whole).
* [[August 15]], Catholic, [[Feast of the Assumption]]
* August 15, 1769, [[Corsica]], birth of [[Napoleon Bonaparte]]
* August 15, 1945, [[Emperor Hirohito]] declares Japan's [[VJ-Day|unconditional surrender]] officially ending the [[World War II|Second World War]].
* August 15, 1945, [[Korea]] became an independent country.
* August 15, 1947, [[India]] became an independent country.
* August 17, 1945, [[Indonesia]] became an independent country.
* [[August 18]], 1920, The [[Nineteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution|Nineteenth Amendment]] is signed, giving US women the right to vote.
* August 19, 1945, [[Vietnam]]'s [[August Revolution]] succeeded.
* August 20, 1083, [[Hungary]]'s [[Stephen I of Hungary|Saint Stephen]] canonized (1001&amp;nbsp;AD), thus becoming the first of the canonized confessor kings.  St. Stephen's day is a national holiday in Hungary as well as an observed holiday for many Hungarian-Americans and other Hungarians around the world.
* August 20, 1991, [[Estonia]] regains its independence, formally leaving the [[Soviet Union]] which had annexed it back in [[World War&amp;nbsp;II]].
* August 21, 1959, [[Hawaii]] became the 50th state of the United States of America. The third Friday of August was designated [[List of U.S. states by date of statehood|Statehood Day]], a state holiday.
* August 25, 1825, [[Uruguay]] became independent from [[Brazil]].
* August 31, 1957, [[Federation of Malaya]] (now [[Malaysia]]) became an independent country.

===Monthlong events in August===
* [[Edinburgh Festival]] is an internationally famous arts festival that takes place during August
* National [[Immunization]] Awareness Month
* National [[Psoriasis]] Awareness Month
* In many European countries, August is the [[Annual leave|holiday]] month for most workers
* The [[Philippines]] celebrates August as the ''Buwan ng Wika'' (&quot;Month of Language&quot;)
* In the [[United States]], August is National Back to School month. Some US School districts and systems return to school in August.
* In the United States, August is National [[Goat Cheese]] Month.&lt;ref&gt;Bober, Mike. [http://www.dcfoodies.com/2008/08/celebrate-natio.html Celebrate National [[Goat Cheese]] Month with Local Favorites], dcfoodies.com&lt;/ref&gt;
* American Adventures Month
* Audio Appreciation Month
* Black Business Month
* Cataract Awareness Month
* Children's Eye Health and Safety Month
* Children's Vision and Learning Month
* Get Ready for Kindergarten Month
* Happiness Happens Month
* Inventors' Month
* [[Neurosurgery]] Outreach Month
* [[Panini]] Month
* [[Spinal Muscular Atrophy]] Awareness Month
* What Will Be Your Legacy Month
* Win with Civility Month&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.mhprofessional.com/?page=/mhp/categories/chases/content/special_months.html MHprofessional.com]&lt;/ref&gt;

===Weeklong events in August===
* During the first week of August in Wales, the [[National Eisteddfod of Wales]] is held, in which many aspects of [[Wales|Welsh]] art and culture are celebrated.
* During the first week of August in Sweden, the Medieval Week of Wisby in Gotland is held each year.
* During the first week of August is World Breastfeeding Week.
* The [[Sturgis Motorcycle Rally]] is held the first full week in August each year.
* The middle week of August is the peak of the [[Perseids|Perseid meteor shower]].
* The [[Pennsic War]], a massive gathering of the [[Society for Creative Anachronism]], takes place about the first week of August every year.
* The first week of August is &quot;Indian Week&quot; for the [[Penobscot people|Penobscot]] [[Tribe]] in [[Old Town, Maine]]. In this week, members of the Penobscot Tribe from all over [[Maine]] venture to the [[Penobscot Indian Island Reservation]] in Old Town and take part in games, [[Indigenous peoples of the Americas|Native American]] arts and crafts, [[pow-wow]]s, cook-outs, etc.

===Other August events===
* The first full weekend in August each year, [[Twinsburg, Ohio]], celebrates [[Twins Days]].
*[[Bon festival]] – (Obon Festival) is a Japanese traditional [[buddhism|buddhist]] custom, evolved into a [[family reunion]] holiday. Many Japanese manufacturers and firms give their employees three to five days off around [[August 15]].

===Daily events in August===
* The Philippines celebrates National Heroes Day in commemoration of the First Cry of the Philippine Revolution on August 23, 1896.

==August symbols==
[[File:Gladiolus imbricatus1002.jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Gladiolus]]]]
August's [[birthstone]] is the [[peridot]] or [[onyx]]. Its [[birth flower]] is the [[gladiolus]] or [[poppy]], meaning beauty, strength of character, love, marriage and family.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.shgresources.com/gems/birthflowers/ Birth months, flowers, and gemstones], shgresources.com&lt;/ref&gt;

