*  [[65]] &amp;ndash; [[Seneca the Younger]], Roman philosopher, statesman, and dramatist
* [[238]] &amp;ndash; [[Gordian I]], [[Roman Emperor]]
*  238   &amp;ndash; [[Gordian II]], heir to the Roman Empire
* [[352]] &amp;ndash; St. [[Pope Julius I|Julius I]], 35th [[Pope]]
* [[434]] &amp;ndash; [[Archbishop Maximianus of Constantinople]]
*[[1125]] &amp;ndash; [[Vladislaus I of Bohemia]] (b. 1065)
*[[1443]] &amp;ndash; [[Henry Chichele]], [[Archbishop of Canterbury]]
*[[1550]] &amp;ndash; [[Claude, Duke of Guise]], French soldier (b. 1496)
*[[1555]] &amp;ndash; [[Juana of Castile]], wife of [[Philip I of Castile]] (b. 1479)
*[[1675]] &amp;ndash; [[Richard Bennett (Governor)|Richard Bennett]], British Colonial Governor of Virginia (b. 1609)
*[[1684]] &amp;ndash; [[Nicolò Amati]], Italian luthier and member of the [[Amati|Amati family]] (b. 1596)
*[[1687]] &amp;ndash; [[Ambrose Dixon]], British-born American settler (b. c. 1619)
