*[[2003]] &amp;ndash; [[Peter 'Possum' Bourne]], New Zealand race car driver (b. 1956)
*  2003   &amp;ndash; [[Wim van Est]], Dutch cyclist (b. 1923)
*  2003   &amp;ndash; [[Mark Berger (economist)|Mark Berger]], [[University of Kentucky]] professor (b. 1955)
*[[2005]] &amp;ndash; [[Ron Todd]], [[TGWU]] General Secretary (1985 &amp;ndash; 1992) (b. 1927)
*[[2006]] &amp;ndash; [[Lawrence Patrick]], Biomechanics Professor, crash test subject (b. 1920)
*  2006   &amp;ndash; [[Pramoedya Ananta Toer]], Indonesian novelist (b. 1925)
*  2006   &amp;ndash; [[Beatriz Sheridan]], Mexican actress and director (b. 1934)
*[[2007]] &amp;ndash; [[Grégory Lemarchal]], French singer (b. 1983)
*  2007   &amp;ndash; [[Kevin Mitchell (football player)|Kevin Mitchell]], American football player (b. 1971)
*  2007   &amp;ndash; [[Tom Poston]], American actor (b. 1921)
*  2007   &amp;ndash; [[Gordon Scott]], American actor (b. 1927)
*  2007   &amp;ndash; [[Zola Taylor]], American singer (b. 1938)
*[[2008]] &amp;ndash; [[John Cargher]], Australian radio broadcaster (b. 1919)
*[[2009]] &amp;ndash; [[Venetia Burney]], Person who suggested Pluto's name for the planet (b. 1918)
* 2009    &amp;ndash; [[Henk Nijdam]], Dutch professional road bicycle rider (b. 1935)
*[[2010]] &amp;ndash; [[Gerry Ryan]], Irish radio broadcaster (b. 1956)
*[[2011]] &amp;ndash; [[Dorjee Khandu]], Indian, Chief Minister of [[Arunachal Pradesh]] (b. 1955)
