{{Day}}

==Events==
* [[392]] &amp;ndash; [[Arbogast (general)|Arbogast]] has [[Eugenius]] elected [[Western Roman Emperor]].
* [[476]] &amp;ndash; [[Odoacer]] is named ''Rex italiae'' by his troops.
* [[565]] &amp;ndash; [[St. Columba]] reports seeing a monster in [[Loch Ness]], [[Scotland]].
* [[851]] &amp;ndash; [[Erispoe]] defeats [[Charles the Bald]] near the Breton town of Jengland.
*[[1138]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of the Standard]] between Scotland and England.
*[[1485]] &amp;ndash; The [[Battle of Bosworth Field]], the death of [[Richard III of England|Richard III]] and the end of the [[House of Plantagenet]].
*[[1559]] &amp;ndash; [[Bartolomé Carranza]], [[Spain|Spanish]] [[archbishop]], is arrested for [[Christian heresy|heresy]].
*[[1639]] &amp;ndash; [[Madras]] (now [[Chennai]]), [[India]], is founded by the [[British East India Company]] on a sliver of land bought from local Nayak rulers.
*[[1642]] &amp;ndash; [[Charles I of England|Charles I]] calls the [[English Parliament]] traitors. The [[English Civil War]] begins.
*[[1654]] &amp;ndash; [[Jacob Barsimson]] arrives in [[New Amsterdam]]. He is the first known [[Judaism|Jewish]] [[Immigration|immigrant]] to America.
*[[1717]] &amp;ndash; [[Spain|Spanish]] troops land on [[Sardinia]].
*[[1770]] &amp;ndash; [[James Cook]]'s expedition lands on the east coast of [[Australia]].
*[[1780]] &amp;ndash; [[James Cook]]'s ship ''[[HMS Resolution (Cook)|HMS Resolution]]'' returns to England (Cook having been killed on [[Hawaii]] during the voyage).
*[[1791]] &amp;ndash; Beginning of the [[Haiti]]an [[Haitian Revolution|Slave Revolution]] in [[Saint-Domingue]].
*[[1798]] &amp;ndash; [[France|French]] troops land in [[Kilcummin|Kilcummin harbour]], [[County Mayo]], [[Ireland]] to aid [[Theobald Wolfe Tone|Wolfe Tone's]] [[Society of the United Irishmen|United Irishmen's]] [[Irish Rebellion of 1798|Irish Rebellion]].
*[[1827]] &amp;ndash; [[José de La Mar]] becomes [[President of Peru]].
*[[1831]] &amp;ndash; [[Nat Turner's slave rebellion]] commences just after midnight in [[Southampton, Virginia]], leading to the deaths of more than 50 whites and several hundred [[African Americans]] who are killed in retaliation for the uprising.
*[[1848]] &amp;ndash; [[United States|The United States]] annexes [[New Mexico]].
*[[1849]] &amp;ndash; The first [[airstrike|air raid]] in history. Austria launches pilotless balloons against the city of [[Venice]].
*[[1851]] &amp;ndash; The first [[America's Cup]] is won by the [[yacht]] ''[[America (yacht)|America]]''.
*[[1864]] &amp;ndash; 12 [[nation]]s sign the First [[Geneva Conventions|Geneva Convention]]. The [[International Red Cross and Red Crescent Movement|Red Cross]] is formed.
*[[1875]] &amp;ndash; The [[Treaty of Saint Petersburg (1875)|Treaty of Saint Petersburg]] between [[Japan]] and [[Russia]] is ratified, providing for the exchange of [[Sakhalin]] for the [[Kuril Islands]].
*[[1902]] &amp;ndash; [[Cadillac]] Motor Company is founded.
*  1902   &amp;ndash; [[Theodore Roosevelt]] becomes the first [[President of the United States]] to ride in an automobile.
&lt;!-- *[[1902]] &amp;ndash; The [[Germany|German]] [[Luger]], later to become the official German sidearm for both World Wars, is first produced. Luger article contradicts this--&gt;
*[[1910]] &amp;ndash; [[Korea]] is annexed by [[Japan]] with the signing of the [[Japan–Korea Annexation Treaty]], beginning a period of Japanese rule of Korea that lasted until the end of World War II.
*[[1911]] &amp;ndash; [[Mona Lisa]] is stolen.
*[[1914]] &amp;ndash; [[World War I]]: in [[Belgium]], [[United Kingdom|British]] and [[Germany|German]] troops clash for the first time in the war.
*[[1922]] &amp;ndash; [[Michael Collins (Irish leader)|Michael Collins]], [[Commander-in-Chief]] of the [[Irish Free State]] Army is shot dead during an [[Irish Republican Army (1922–1969)|Anti-Treaty]] ambush at [[Béal na mBláth]], [[County Cork]], during the [[Irish Civil War]].
*[[1926]] &amp;ndash; [[Gold]] is discovered in [[Johannesburg]], [[South Africa]].
*[[1932]] &amp;ndash; The [[BBC]] first experiments with television broadcasting. (See also [[Timeline of the BBC#1930s|Timeline of the BBC]].)
*[[1934]] &amp;ndash; [[Bill Woodfull]] of [[australia national cricket team|Australia]] becomes the only [[cricket]] captain to twice regain [[The Ashes]].
*[[1941]] &amp;ndash; [[World War II]]: [[Germany|German]] [[troop]]s reach [[Saint Petersburg|Leningrad]], leading to the [[siege of Leningrad]].
*[[1942]] &amp;ndash; World War II: [[Brazil]] [[History of Brazil (1930-1945)#World War II|declares war]] on [[Germany]] and [[Italy]].
*[[1944]] &amp;ndash; World War II: [[Romania]] is captured by the [[Soviet Union]].
*  1944   &amp;ndash; World War II: [[Holocaust of Kedros]] in [[Crete]] by German forces
*[[1949]] &amp;ndash; [[1949 Queen Charlotte earthquake|Queen Charlotte earthquake]]: Canada's largest earthquake since the [[1700 Cascadia earthquake]]
*[[1950]] &amp;ndash; [[Althea Gibson]] becomes the first black [[Competition|competitor]] in international [[tennis]].
*[[1952]] &amp;ndash; The [[penal colony]] on [[Devil's Island]] is permanently closed.
*[[1962]] &amp;ndash; An attempt to assassinate [[France|French]] [[president]] [[Charles de Gaulle]] fails.
*  1962   &amp;ndash; The [[NS Savannah|NS ''Savannah'']], the world's first [[Nuclear marine propulsion|nuclear-powered]] cargo ship, completes its [[maiden voyage]].
*[[1963]] &amp;ndash; American [[Joseph A. Walker|Joe Walker]] in an [[X-15]] test plane reaches an altitude of {{convert|106|km|mi|abbr=on|lk=off}}.
*[[1966]] &amp;ndash; Labor movements [[NFWA]] and AWOC merge to become the United Farm Workers Organizing Committee (UFWOC), predecessor of the [[United Farm Workers]].
*[[1968]] &amp;ndash; [[Pope Paul VI]] arrives in [[Bogotá]], [[Colombia]]. It is the first visit of a [[pope]] to [[Latin America]].
*[[1971]] &amp;ndash; [[J. Edgar Hoover]] and [[John N. Mitchell|John Mitchell]] announce the arrest of 20 of the [[Camden 28]].
*[[1972]] &amp;ndash; [[Rhodesia]] is expelled by the [[International Olympic Committee|IOC]] for its racist policies.
*[[1978]] &amp;ndash; The ''[[Sandinista National Liberation Front|Frente Sandinista de Liberacion]]'' or [[FSLN]] occupies national palace in [[Nicaragua]].
*[[1985]] &amp;ndash; [[British Airtours Flight 28M|Manchester Air Disaster]] sees 55 people killed when a [[fire]] breaks out on a commercial aircraft at [[Manchester Airport]].
*[[1989]] &amp;ndash; The first [[planetary ring|ring]] of [[Neptune]] is discovered.
*  1989   &amp;ndash; [[Nolan Ryan]] strikes out [[Rickey Henderson]] to become the first [[Major League Baseball]] [[pitcher]] to record 5,000 [[strikeout]]s.
*[[1992]] &amp;ndash; [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]] [[Hostage Rescue Team|HRT]] [[sniper]] [[Lon Horiuchi]] shoots and kills Vicki Weaver during an 11-day siege at her home at [[Ruby Ridge]], [[Idaho]].
*[[1996]] &amp;ndash; [[Bill Clinton]] signs [[PRWORA|welfare reform]] into law, representing major shift in US welfare policy
*[[2003]] &amp;ndash; [[Alabama]] [[Chief Justice]] [[Roy Moore]] is suspended after refusing to comply with a federal court order to remove a rock inscribed with the [[Ten Commandments]] from the lobby of the [[Alabama Supreme Court]] building.
*[[2004]] &amp;ndash; A version of ''[[The Scream]]'' and ''[[Madonna (Edvard Munch)|Madonna]]'', two paintings by [[Edvard Munch]], are stolen at gunpoint from a museum in [[Oslo]], [[Norway]].
*[[2006]] &amp;ndash; [[Pulkovo Aviation Enterprise Flight 612]] crashes near the [[Russia]]n border over eastern [[Ukraine]], killing all 170 people on board.
*[[2007]] &amp;ndash; The [[Texas Rangers (baseball)|Texas Rangers]] rout the [[Baltimore Orioles]] 30-3, the most runs scored by a team in modern MLB history.
*  2007   &amp;ndash; The [[Storm botnet]], a botnet created by the [[Storm Worm]], sends out a record 57 million e-mails in one day

