==Deaths==
&lt;!-- Do not add people without Wikipedia articles to this list; do not trust &quot;this year in history&quot; websites for accurate date information; do not link multiple occurrences of the same year, just link the first occurrence.--&gt;
* [[408]] &amp;ndash; [[Stilicho]], Roman general (b. 359)
*[[1155]] &amp;ndash; [[Emperor Konoe|Konoe]], Emperor of Japan (b. 1139)
*[[1188]] &amp;ndash; [[Ferdinand II of Leon|Ferdinand II]], King of Leon (b. 1137)
*[[1241]] &amp;ndash; [[Pope Gregory IX]], (b. c.1143)
*[[1280]] &amp;ndash; [[Pope Nicholas III]] (b. c.1216)
*[[1304]] &amp;ndash; [[John II, Count of Hainaut]] (b. 1247)
*[[1350]] &amp;ndash; [[Philip VI of France|Philip VI]], King of France (b. 1293)
*[[1358]] &amp;ndash; [[Isabella of France|Isabella, Queen of England]] (b. c. 1295)
*[[1485]] &amp;ndash; [[Richard III of England|Richard III]], King of England (b. 1452)
*[[1553]] &amp;ndash; [[John Dudley, 1st Duke of Northumberland]], English admiral and politician (b. 1504)
*[[1572]] &amp;ndash; [[Thomas Percy, 7th Earl of Northumberland]] (b. 1528)
*[[1584]] &amp;ndash; [[Jan Kochanowski]], Polish writer (b. 1530)
*[[1599]] &amp;ndash; [[Luca Marenzio]], Italian composer (b. c.1553)
*[[1607]] &amp;ndash; [[Bartholomew Gosnold]], English explorer and privateer (b. 1572)
*[[1609]] &amp;ndash; [[Judah Loew ben Bezalel|Maharal of Prague]], Jewish mystic and philosopher (b. 1525)
*[[1652]] &amp;ndash; [[Jacob De la Gardie]], Swedish soldier and statesman (b. 1583)
*[[1680]] &amp;ndash; [[John George II, Elector of Saxony]] (b. 1613)
*[[1701]] &amp;ndash; [[John Granville, 1st Earl of Bath]], English royalist statesman (b. 1628)
*[[1711]] &amp;ndash; [[Louis François, duc de Boufflers]], French marshal (b. 1644)
*[[1752]] &amp;ndash; [[William Whiston]], English mathematician (b. 1667)
*[[1773]] &amp;ndash; [[George Lyttelton, 1st Baron Lyttelton|George Lyttelton]], English writer and politician (b. 1709)
*[[1793]] &amp;ndash; [[Louis, 4th duc de Noailles]], Marshal of France (b. 1713)
*  1793   &amp;ndash; [[Cäcilia Weber]], German mother-in-law of [[Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart]] (b. 1727)
*[[1797]] &amp;ndash; [[Dagobert Sigmund von Wurmser]], Alsatian-born Austrian general (b. 1724)
*[[1806]] &amp;ndash; [[Jean-Honoré Fragonard]], French artist (b. 1732)
